1. Pick / Non-Pick Approach (Binary Decision Tree)Is approach mein aap har element ke samne khade hokar sirf 2 choices lete hain: "Is element ko lu ya na lu?"Dimaag mein chalne waali soch: Ek baar element ko lekar aage badho, ek baar bina liye aage badho.Recursion Calls: Ismein hamesha do alag-alag recursion calls likhi jaati hain.Recursion Call Ka Funda:C++
// CHOICE 1: PICK (Element ko temp mein daala)
temp.push_back(candidates[index]);
solve(index, target - candidates[index]); // Same index kyunki repeat kar sakte hain
// (Agar repeat nahi kar sakte hote, toh index + 1 bhejte)

temp.pop_back(); // Backtrack (Rasta saaf kiya)(pehle jaise state pe pahuche)

// CHOICE 2: NON-PICK (Bina element ko liye agle par chale gaye)
solve(index + 1, target); // Index badal gaya, par target SAME raha
Kab use karein? Jab aapko "Subsets", "Subsequences" nikaalne hon, ya jab fixed do hi raaste hon (Yes/No).

2.For-Loop Approach (Multi-Way Decision Tree)Is approach mein aap ek index par khade hokar aage ke saare available options (elements) par ek saath nazar daalte hain.Dimaag mein chalne waali soch: Main abhi jis position par hoon, wahan array ka kaun-kaun sa element fit baith sakta hai? Main ek-ek karke sabko try karunga.Recursion Calls: Ismein loop ke andar sirf EK recursion call hoti hai, kyunki non-pick ka kaam loop khud handle kar leta hai.Recursion Call Ka Funda:C++for (int i = index; i < candidates.size(); i++) {
    // 1. DO: Jo option pasand aaya, use pick karo
    temp.push_back(candidates[i]);
    
    // 2. EXPLORE: Agli call lagao.only pick ki call lgegi non pick khud handle karlega loop
    solve(i, target - candidates[i]); // 'i' bheja kyunki element repeat ho sakta hai
    // (Agar repeat nahi kar sakte hote, toh 'i + 1' bhejte)
    
    // 3. UNDO: Backtrack karo taaki loop agle element 'i+1' ko try kar sake
    temp.pop_back(); 
}
Kab use karein? Jab "Combinations", "Permutations" nikaalne hon, ya jab array mein se elements ko aage-piche chunne ki choices zyada hon.💡 Confusion Door Karne Wali Ultimate Cheat SheetAapko recursion call likhte waat bas 2 sawaal khud se poochne hain:Sawaal 1: Kya element REPEAT ho sakta hai?Haan (Infinite Supply): Recursion call mein hamesha current variable hi bhejo (Pick/Non-Pick mein index, For-Loop mein i).Naa (Use Only Once): Recursion call mein hamesha agla index bhejo (Pick/Non-Pick mein index + 1, For-Loop mein i + 1).Sawaal 2: Target ke sath kya karein?Agar element ko PUSH kiya hai (temp.push_back): Toh target hamesha kam hoga $\rightarrow$ target - candidates[...].Agar element ko PUSH nahi kiya (Sirf Pick/Non-Pick ki second call mein): Toh target SAME rahega $\rightarrow$ target.Agli baar jab question samne aaye, toh pehle tay karo ki Method 1 (Binary) lagana hai ya Method 2 (Loop). Uske baad bas upar diye gaye 2 sawaal khud se poocho, recursion call bina kisi darr ke sahi likhi jayegi!
